.TH "lpfc_create_port" 9 "lpfc_create_port" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_create_port \- Create an FC port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct lpfc_vport *" lpfc_create_port
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "int instance "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
pointer to lpfc hba data structure.
.IP "instance" 12
a unique integer ID to this FC port.
.IP "dev" 12
pointer to the device data structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine creates a FC port for the upper layer protocol. The FC port
can be created on top of either a physical port or a virtual port provided
by the HBA. This routine also allocates a SCSI host data structure (shost)
and associates the FC port created before adding the shost into the SCSI
layer.

Return codes
\fIvport\fP - pointer to the virtual N_Port data structure.
NULL - port create failed.
